# Generate HTML for a simple recipe
<<<
>> title: Boiled potatoes
>> servings: 2
>> course: dinner
Put @Potatoes{4} in a #pan and add @water{1%L} and some @salt.

Boil for 12 minutes.
$$$ nix run .# 2> /dev/null | tidy -quiet -indent -wrap 1000 --tidy-mark false
>>>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="course" content="dinner">
  <title>Boiled potatoes</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Boiled potatoes</h1>
  <h2>Ingredients (serves 2)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>potatoes, 4.0</li>
    <li>water, 1.0 L</li>
    <li>salt</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>Instructions</h2>
  <p>Put 4.0 Potatoes in a pan and add 1.0 L water and some salt.</p>
  <p>Boil for 12 minutes.</p>
</body>
</html>

